headline: Microsoft & Meta earnings, Fed's rate decision: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton outlines the biggest stories to watch on Wednesday, Jul. 30. Microsoft (MSFT), Meta (META), Qualcomm (QCOM), Arm Holdings (ARM), Robinhood (HOOD), and Ford (FORD) will report quarterly earnings results after the markets close. The Federal Reserve's FOMC meeting will continue into its second day. At 2 p.m., Chairman Jerome Powell will announce whether interest rates will be cut or held steady. Tune in to Yahoo Finance on Wednesday at 2 p.m. for coverage of the Fed's rate decision. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: Teradyne beats quarterly revenue estimates on robust chip-testing demand
summary: Companies such as Teradyne, which make testing tools for chips, have seen a surge in demand as semiconductor makers invest in quality control while scaling up capacity to meet an artificial intelligence-led boom.  Teradyne designs and develops technology for chips and electronic equipment testing, and also sells robotic systems to customers in the manufacturing sector.  On an adjusted basis, Teradyne earned 57 cents per share, compared with estimates of 54 cents apiece.

headline: Numecent Releases Support for Windows on Arm, Enabling Application Compatibility Across Next-Generation Windows Devices
summary: Numecent, a leader in application containerization and cloud-native application delivery, today announced that its Cloudpaging Player now supports Windows on Arm (WoA). With this release, Numecent is the first application virtualization and container management solution provider to extend native support to Windows on Arm devices, ensuring containerized applications can seamlessly run on the next generation of Windows devices powered by Arm-based processors, such as Qualcomm's Snapdragon platform
